===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}

{{w|Oracle bone script}} and {{w|bronze inscription}}s: a {{liushu|p|nocap=y}} of a filled container, the original form of {{och-l|賜|to confer, to bestow}}. Possibly specialised from {{och-l|益|to increase, to add}}. Perhaps borrowed phonetically to mean "easy".

The character is not the pictogram of a [[chameleon]], as folk etymology says. Unrelated to [[陽]] since it doesn't represent the [[sun]].

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|ss=𠃓}}
From {{och-l|移|to change; to alter}} + k-extension ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). The meaning of "change, alter" is linked to "give, bestow" since something given by somebody to somebody else "changes" its owner.

